Title: Modeling Interactive 3D and Multimedia Animation with an Embedded Language  
Author: Conal Elliott 
Web: http://www.research.microsoft.com/~conal  
Affiliation: Microsoft Research  
Abstract: We propose that this situation can be improved by a change of language, and present Fran, synthesized by complementing an existing declarative host language, Haskell, with an embedded domainspecific vocabulary for modeled animation. As demonstrated in a collection of examples, the resulting animation descriptions are not only relatively easy to write, but also highly composable. 
